# Load the data
features <- read.csv("features.csv")
stores <- read.csv("stores.csv")
train <- read.csv("train.csv")
test <- read.csv("test.csv")

# Optional: Train on one store for experimentation
# train <- train %>% filter(Store == 20)
# Merge Datasets and Convert Dates
train$Date <- as.Date(train$Date, format = "%Y-%m-%d")
features$Date <- as.Date(features$Date, format = "%Y-%m-%d")
train_data <- train %>%
  left_join(features, by = c("Store", "Date")) %>%
  left_join(stores, by = "Store")
train_data[is.na(train_data)] <- 0
# Convert categorical columns to integer
train_data$IsHoliday.x <- as.integer(as.factor(train_data$IsHoliday.x))
train_data$Type <- as.integer(as.factor(train_data$Type))
train_data$Store <- as.integer(as.factor(train_data$Store))
train_data$Dept <- as.integer(as.factor(train_data$Dept))
train_data$Month <- as.integer(format(train_data$Date, "%m"))

store_labels_full <- train_data$Store
dept_labels_full <- train_data$Dept

# Remove duplicate column and reorder
train_data <- train_data %>%
  select(-IsHoliday.y) %>%
  relocate(Store, Dept, .after = Date)
# Normalize numeric predictors and target
numeric_features <- train_data %>%
  select(-Date, -Weekly_Sales) %>%
  select_if(is.numeric)

scaled_features <- scale(numeric_features)
weekly_sales_scaled <- scale(train_data$Weekly_Sales)
weekly_sales_center <- attr(weekly_sales_scaled, "scaled:center")
weekly_sales_scale <- attr(weekly_sales_scaled, "scaled:scale")

train_data_scaled <- bind_cols(Weekly_Sales = as.vector(weekly_sales_scaled),
                               as.data.frame(scaled_features))
# Create lagged features with adjustable window size
lagm <- function(x, k) {
  pad = matrix(NA, k, ncol(x))
  n = nrow(x)
  rbind(pad, x[1:(n - k), ])
}

LAG <- 6  # Can be tuned: 6 or 8 is good for capturing monthly cycles
xdata <- as.matrix(train_data_scaled)

arframe <- data.frame(Weekly_Sales = xdata[,1])
for (i in 1:LAG) {
  arframe <- bind_cols(arframe, as.data.frame(lagm(xdata, i)))
}
## New names:
## New names:
## New names:
## New names:
## New names:
## New names:
## • `Weekly_Sales` -> `Weekly_Sales...1`
## • `Weekly_Sales` -> `Weekly_Sales...2`
arframe <- arframe[-c(1:LAG), ]
# Reshape for LSTM
n <- nrow(arframe)
p <- ncol(arframe) / LAG
xrnn <- array(data.matrix(arframe[, -1]), dim = c(n, LAG, p))
# Train/test split and adjust labels
train_split_flag <- train_data$Date < as.Date("2011-10-01")
train_split_flag <- train_split_flag[-c(1:LAG)]
store_labels <- store_labels_full[-c(1:LAG)]
dept_labels <- dept_labels_full[-c(1:LAG)]

# Count number of training vs. total observations (after lag removal)
total_rows <- length(train_split_flag)
train_rows <- sum(train_split_flag)
test_rows <- total_rows - train_rows

# Print ratio
cat("Train Set Proportion:", round(train_rows / total_rows * 100, 2), "%\n")
## Train Set Proportion: 60.57 %
cat("Test Set Proportion:", round(test_rows / total_rows * 100, 2), "%\n")
## Test Set Proportion: 39.43 %
# Define and build the model with stacked LSTM and embeddings
store_input <- layer_input(shape = 1, dtype = 'int32', name = 'store_input')
dept_input <- layer_input(shape = 1, dtype = 'int32', name = 'dept_input')

store_embed <- store_input %>%
  layer_embedding(input_dim = max(store_labels) + 1, output_dim = 5, input_length = 1) %>%
  layer_flatten()

dept_embed <- dept_input %>%
  layer_embedding(input_dim = max(dept_labels) + 1, output_dim = 5, input_length = 1) %>%
  layer_flatten()

features_input <- layer_input(shape = c(LAG, p), name = 'features_input')
lstm_output <- features_input %>%
  layer_lstm(units = 128, return_sequences = TRUE, dropout = 0.2, recurrent_dropout = 0.1) %>%
  layer_lstm(units = 64, dropout = 0.1)

combined <- layer_concatenate(list(lstm_output, store_embed, dept_embed)) %>%
  layer_dense(units = 1)

model <- keras_model(inputs = list(features_input, store_input, dept_input), outputs = combined)

model %>% compile(
  loss = 'mse',
  optimizer = 'adam',
  metrics = c('mse')
)

model %>% fit(
  list(features_input = xrnn[train_split_flag,,],
       store_input = store_labels[train_split_flag],
       dept_input = dept_labels[train_split_flag]),
  arframe[train_split_flag, 1],
  batch_size = 256,
  epochs = 25
)

# Evaluate
predictions <- model %>% predict(
  list(features_input = xrnn[!train_split_flag,,],
       store_input = store_labels[!train_split_flag],
       dept_input = dept_labels[!train_split_flag])
)
## 5194/5194 - 6s - 6s/epoch - 1ms/step
predictions_rescaled <- predictions * weekly_sales_scale + weekly_sales_center
actual_rescaled <- arframe[!train_split_flag, 1] * weekly_sales_scale + weekly_sales_center

mse <- mean((predictions_rescaled - actual_rescaled)^2)
mae <- mean(abs(predictions_rescaled - actual_rescaled))
rmse <- sqrt(mse)
nonzero_mask <- actual_rescaled > 100
mape <- mean(abs((actual_rescaled[nonzero_mask] - predictions_rescaled[nonzero_mask]) / actual_rescaled[nonzero_mask])) * 100
ss_res <- sum((actual_rescaled - predictions_rescaled)^2)
ss_tot <- sum((actual_rescaled - mean(actual_rescaled))^2)
r_squared <- 1 - (ss_res / ss_tot)

cat("Test MSE:", mse, "\n")
## Test MSE: 160513897
cat("Mean Absolute Error:", round(mae, 2), "\n")
## Mean Absolute Error: 7243
cat("Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE):", round(rmse, 2), "\n")
## Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE): 12669.41
cat("Mean Absolute Percentage Error (MAPE):", round(mape, 2), "%\n")
## Mean Absolute Percentage Error (MAPE): 294.78 %
cat("R-squared (R²):", round(r_squared, 4), "\n")
## R-squared (R²): 0.7003
# Visualize overall
plot(actual_rescaled, type = 'l', main = 'Actual vs Predicted Sales', ylab = 'Weekly Sales')
lines(predictions_rescaled, col = 'red')
legend("topright", legend = c("Actual", "Predicted"), col = c("black", "red"), lty = 1)

# R² by Store
r2_df <- data.frame(
  Store = store_labels[!train_split_flag],
  Actual = as.vector(actual_rescaled),
  Predicted = as.vector(predictions_rescaled)
)

r2_by_store <- r2_df %>%
  group_by(Store) %>%
  summarise(
    SS_Res = sum((Actual - Predicted)^2),
    SS_Tot = sum((Actual - mean(Actual))^2),
    R2 = 1 - (SS_Res / SS_Tot)
  ) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  arrange(R2)

# Plot R² Scores
ggplot(r2_by_store, aes(x = reorder(as.factor(Store), R2), y = R2, fill = R2)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  coord_flip() +
  scale_fill_viridis(option = "C", direction = -1) +
  labs(title = "R² Scores by Store (LSTM Model)", x = "Store ID", y = "R² Score") +
  theme_minimal()

# Create plot function
gen_store_plot <- function(store_id, df) {
  df_store <- df %>% filter(Store == store_id) %>% mutate(Index = row_number())
  ggplot(df_store, aes(x = Index)) +
    geom_line(aes(y = Actual, color = "Actual")) +
    geom_line(aes(y = Predicted, color = "Predicted"), linetype = "dashed") +
    labs(title = paste("Store", store_id), y = "Weekly Sales", x = NULL) +
    scale_color_manual(values = c("Actual" = "blue", "Predicted" = "red")) +
    theme_minimal()
}

# Create store-level plots
top_plots <- lapply(top_stores, gen_store_plot, df = r2_df)
bottom_plots <- lapply(bottom_stores, gen_store_plot, df = r2_df)

plot_store_forecast <- function(store_id) {
  df_store <- r2_df %>% filter(Store == store_id)
  plot(df_store$Actual, type = 'l', col = 'blue', lwd = 2,
       main = paste("Store", store_id), ylab = "Weekly Sales", xlab = "Date", xaxt = 'n')
  lines(df_store$Predicted, col = 'red', lwd = 2, lty = 2)
  axis(1, at = seq(1, nrow(df_store), length.out = 4),
       labels = format(seq(as.Date("2011-10-01"), length.out = 4, by = "3 months"), "%b"))
  legend("topright", legend = c("Actual Sales", "Predicted Sales"),
         col = c("blue", "red"), lty = c(1, 2), cex = 0.8)
}

# Helper: Calculate store-level metrics
store_metrics <- r2_df %>%
  group_by(Store) %>%
  summarise(
    MAE = mean(abs(Actual - Predicted)),
    MSE = mean((Actual - Predicted)^2),
    RMSE = sqrt(MSE),
    MAPE = mean(abs((Actual - Predicted) / Actual)[Actual != 0], na.rm = TRUE) * 100,
    R2 = 1 - sum((Actual - Predicted)^2) / sum((Actual - mean(Actual))^2)
  ) %>%
  ungroup()

plot_store_forecast <- function(store_id) {
  df_store <- r2_df %>% filter(Store == store_id)
  plot(df_store$Actual, type = 'l', col = 'blue', lwd = 2,
       main = paste("Store", store_id), ylab = "Weekly Sales", xlab = "Date", xaxt = 'n')
  lines(df_store$Predicted, col = 'red', lwd = 2, lty = 2)
  axis(1, at = seq(1, nrow(df_store), length.out = 4),
       labels = format(seq(as.Date("2011-10-01"), length.out = 4, by = "3 months"), "%b"))
  legend("topright", legend = c("Actual Sales", "Predicted Sales"),
         col = c("blue", "red"), lty = c(1, 2), bty = "n", cex = 0.8)
}
